name: integer_u64_alternating_ones
description: |
  This checkerboard bit pattern alternates 1 and 0 across the entire u64
  value and has the sign bit set. Together with its complement it catches stuck
  bits, incorrect masks, shift errors, and signed intermediates.
format: hex
decode-as: u64
pair:
  - with: alternating-zeroes.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u64"
  - "alternating-bits"
  - "bitwise"
  - "shift"
  - "mask"
  - "canary"
---
aa aa aa aa aa aa aa aa # 0xaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa
